      <p permid="bCV">
          Let <m>\phi:G \to H</m> be a homomorphism with kernel <m>K</m>.  Prove that <m>\phi</m> is injective (one-to-one) if and only if <m>K = \{e\}</m>.  (That is, if and only if the <em>only</em> element in the kernel is the identity.)  
